if I factor out an dependency with `--external`&`--require` to a second bundle and want to lazily load it later when needed with a script loader it fails with a weird error:

```
Uncaught Error: Cannot find module 'VTjjby' 
```
## Code

build:

```
browserify -x ./graph.js  ./main.js > main-bundle.js
browserify -r ./graph.js > graph-bundle.js
```

index.html:

``` html
...
<!-- only main bundle here! -->
<script src="main-bundle.js"></script>
...
```

main.js:

``` javascript
var btn = document.querySelectorAll(".show-graph")[0];
btn.addEventListener("click", function(){
  loadScript("graph-bundle.js", function(){
    // Executed when the graph-bundle.js is fully loaded
    var drawGraph = require("./graph"); // BOOM
    document.body.innerHTML = drawGraph();
  });
});
```
## Rationale

In this app it is crucial that the page loads instantly, but it also has a rarely used "view graph" feature which requires a huge graph library and I want to load it only when user uses it

